==Turkish==
'''-a''' (''in words with back vowel harmony''); '''-e''' (''in words with front vowel harmony'')

===Suffix===
#Used to form the [[dative]] case.

===Alternative forms===
*[[-ya]], [[-ye]] (''after a vowel''); [[-na]], [[-ne]] (''after a possessive'')

====Examples====
*''İstanbul'a'' - to Istanbul
*''Ankara'ya'' = to Ankara
*''İzmir'e'' = to Izmir
*''babasına'' = to his father

===Suffix===
#Used to form [[gerund]]s.

'''-a''' (''in words with back vowel harmony''); '''-e''' (''in words with front vowel harmony'')

===Alternative forms===
*[[-ya]], [[-ye]] (''after a vowel'')

====Examples====
*''yürüye yürüye'' - by walking

